    <text>
        <body>
            <div1 type="calendarCollection">
                <!--div1 just wraps the whole collection. -->
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-12"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/march/1909-03-12.jpg">
                    <!--div2 is for each calendar entry. 
                 1. We can construct an xml:id (to hold a distinct identifier) for this entry:
              it is just the letter "e" followed by the yyyy-mm-dd for the entry, with each piece separated by a hyphen.
                 2. the @facs attribute points to the web URL where we're hosting the calendar images.
              -->
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-12">March 12, 1909. <lb/>Friday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#multicolor">
                        <figDesc resp="#zmurphy">Drawing of a woman in snowshoes named Molly pointing
                            ahead of her. This is along the left-hand side of the page.</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil">
                        <lb/>Molly on <lb/>snowshoes <lb/>that <persName>Mr. Weir</persName> <lb/>got. <lb/>Pretty picture
                        <lb/>is it not?!</ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" place="bottom-right">Love from Molly</add></ab>
                </div2>
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-02-16"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/docs/photos/february/1909-02-16.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-02-16"> February 16, 1909. <lb/>Tuesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#blackandwhite">
                        <figDesc resp="#zmurphy"> A man by the water looking through a magnifying glass.
                            <ab typed="blackink"> <!-- finish trasncribing here -->
                </div2>
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-02-17"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/docs/photos/february/1909-02-17.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-02-17">February 17, 1909. <lb/>Wednesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil" rend"#cursive">
                        <lb/> Each morning very early <lb/> When all is dark and still<lb/> <persName>Earnest</persName> goes off into likely blaclness <lb/>To work at Hammermill <lb/> I really think he's very good <lb/>to get up when it's dark <lb/> tho he says he doesn't mind <lb/> It cant (blank) (blank) a lark!
                    </ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="bottom-right">(blank) is it still dark when you arise?</add></ab>
                </div2>
                
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-08"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/docs/photos/march/1909-03-08.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-08">March 8, 1909. <lb/>Monday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#redink">
                        <figDesc resp="#zmurphy">A large question mark in the center of the paper.</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="bottom-right">.. this is the day, this...later. done. the</add></ab> <!-- finish trasncribing here -->
                </div2>
                
                
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-12"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/march/1909-03-12.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-12">March 12, 1909. <lb/>Friday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#multicolor">
                        <figDesc resp="#zmurphy">Drawing of a woman in snowshoes named Molly pointing
                            ahead of her. This is along the left-hand side of the page.</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil">
                        <lb/>Molly on <lb/>snowshoes <lb/>that <persName>Mr. Weir</persName> <lb/>got. <lb/>Pretty picture
                        <lb/>is it not?!</ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="bottom-right">Love from Molly</add></ab>
                </div2>
                
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-17"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/march/1909-03-12.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-17">March 17, 1909. <lb/>Wednesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#brownink">
                        <figDesc resp="#zmurphy" place="bottom-right" "top half of the paper" "dispersed" > Green Shambrocks dispersed throughout the paper. Two snakes drawn on the top of the paper. A drawing of the hammerill center bottom right croner. . </figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#brownink">
                        <lb/>ST. Patrick was a usefuf saint<lb/> He frightened all the snakes away- <lb/>I wish he'd try his art on smoke  <lb/>around the hammermill some day! 
                        <lb/>is it not?!</ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" >The Hammermill really lucky!</add></ab>  <!-- finish trasncribing here -->
                </div2>
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-23"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/docs/photos/march/1909-03-23.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-23">March 23, 1909. <lb/>Tuesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#oencil">
                        <figDesc resp="#zmurphy">Drawing of clothes hanging up to dry.</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil">
                        <lb/>Wash day at the berhends <lb/>oh, I say! <lb/>That's really a very  <lb/>unusual display! 
                    </ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="bottom-right">Do you still miss me?</add></ab> 
                </div2>
                
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-25"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/docs/photos/march/1909-03-25.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-25">March 25, 1909. <lb/>Thursday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#multicolor">
                        <figDesc resp="#zmurphy">A woman walking in a garden</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil">
                        <title> At the Lavers </title>
                        <lb/>"Ill send the bill to <persName>Ernst</persName> <lb/> and take them every one <lb/>I'll watch his face &amp;see him <lb/>smile <lb/>It will be such jolly fun!"
                    </ab> 
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="top-right">Molly reviewing a full Gig bill Poor Ernst</add></ab> <!-- finish trasncribing here -->
                </div2>
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-30"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/docs/photos/march/1909-03-30.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-30">March 30, 1909. <lb/>Tuesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#multicolor">
                        <figDesc resp="#zmurphy">Two bunnies dressed up.</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil">
                        <lb/>Latest styles <lb/> in here dressing </ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive" place="bottom-right">Do thee like? </add></ab> 
                </div2>
                
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-03-31"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/docs/photos/march/1909-03-31.jpg">
                    
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-03-31">March 31, 1909. <lb/>Wednesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure hand="#multicolor">
                        <figDesc resp="#zmurphy">A person in their bedroom waking up out of bed.</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#pencil">
                        <lb/>4:30 AM  <lb/>snowshoes <lb/> An early spring."
                        <lb/>is it not?!</ab>
                    <ab><add hand="#redPen" rend="#cursive"place="bottom-right"> <lb/> This is you spring out <lb/> of bed, ready to mruder <lb/> the alarm clock!</add></ab> 
                </div2>
                
                <div2 xml:id="e-1909-07-13"
                    facs="https://arrowarchive.github.io/behrendcalendar/photos/july/1909-07-13.jpg">
                    <fw place="top-center" hand="#calendarPub">COPYRIGHT 1908, BY FRIENDSHIP CALENDAR CO.
                        NEW BRITAIN, CONN.</fw>
                    <ab hand="#calendarPub">
                        <lb/><date when="1909-07-13">July 13, 1909. <lb/>Tuesday</date>
                    </ab>
                    <figure rend="cutout">
                        <figDesc resp="#rgerzevske #ebeshero"><!--ebb: As I zoom in on the image, it's clear this is printed, probably cut out from a magazine. -->
                            An infant is seen from behind. Looking closely, the
                            image was made with a different type of paper. It was likely first printed in a magazine, cut
                            out, and glued onto the page.</figDesc>
                    </figure>
                    <ab hand="#blackPen" rend="smallcaps">
                        <!--ODD addition: customize @rend to "smallcaps" or "cursive" -->
                        <lb/>That little spot in the 
                        <lb/>back of his neck 
                        <lb/>is the sweetest spot to
                        <lb/>kiss I know 
                        <lb/>so I kiss him there 
                        <lb/>and <emph style="underline">hold him close</emph>
                        <lb/>just because I love him so.</ab>
                    
                    <note resp="#rgerzevske">It's clear that Mary is talking about her son Warren here. From the way she
                        talks about him, he is a few months old (or less) and she absolutely adores him.
                        If Warren is her first born child, then her joy from being around him makes a lot
                        more sense. </note>
                </div2>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>

